oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Original wills, Akins, Eli, 1903 May 19
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A typescript copy of the will of Eli Akins, of Chicago, Illinois, dated December 26th, 1902. Illustrates the first page of the document, referring to a realty lot in “G. W. Harding’s plan of lots as registered in the registers office of Davidson County ….” And that “will approved and admitted to record in open court this 13th day of May, A. D. 1903, Charles S. Cutting, Probate Judge and then probated in the City of Chicago on May 19th, 1903. Forms part of Record Group 16, Original Wills, 1780-1925.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Akins family
